Could MORE Chinese products be banned?! A combination of unique factors has put some Chinese technologies on U.S. lawmakers‚Äô naughty list. It‚Äôs hard to buy an internet-connected home device that doesn‚Äôt run on Chinese technology. Technologies that originate in other countries considered adversaries of the United States, such as Iran and Russia, are mostly irrelevant in the United States. There‚Äôs also a fuzzy line in China between private corporations and the government. U.S. officials believe that TikTok or other Chinese companies would have to comply if Beijing ordered them to hand over data they have on Americans, to spy on us, or to spread Chinese Communist Party propaganda.

voice_to_text: please tell me you know who this man is he's a bit mysterious the utimate enigma considered one of the greatest songwriters of all time it's Bob Dylan üòé there is a movie coming out about him a biopic called A Complete Unknown starring Timoth√©e Chalamet who's playing a young Bob Dylan A Complete Unknown is diving into Dylan's meteoric rise between 1961 and 1965 I thought why not dig into the real Bob Dylan you know the one behind the harmonica and the poetry the one that dated muses got married in secret and pulled out a surprise divorce kid out of nowhere so buckle up buttercups it's about to get messy before Bob Dylan became Bob Dylan he was Bobby Zimmerman from Minnesota and Echo Helstrom was the it girl of hiving high school Echo was the blueprint of the bohemian type women that he would surround himself with later and many believe she was the inspiration for some of his early music fast forward to Greenwich Village in the early 60s where Bob meets Suze Rotolo the woman who will forever be immortalized on the cover of his Freewheelin‚Äô album Suze was an artist and a political activist who introduced Bob to leftist politics which influenced his music in the film Elle Fanning is playing a character named Sylvie which is based on Suze can you see it their relationship was passionate but very messy Bob's career was taking off and he had a wandering eye enter folk singer Joan Baez she was already successful with her own album and she invited Bob to perform with her they started bumping uglies but soon he began to treat her like she was extra baggage she said he was demoralizing and they broke up later he apologized to her and they began performing together again I think we're gonna see this dynamic in the film as well by the mid 60s Bob's career is on fire and so is his love life enter Sara Lownds Sara was a former Playboy Bunny and a single mom they got married in 1965 Bob adopted her first daughter Maria and together they had four children three boys one girl Jesse Dylan who is a filmmaker daughter Anna Dylan who unlike some of her brothers is living more of a private life Sam Dylan who also stays a bit more private and then we've got Jakob Dylan also a singer and a songwriter lead vocalist of the Wallflowers who to me looks like a cuter version of his dad Bob and Sara were together for 12 years they grew apart he cheated on her they got divorced and Bob was doing his thing Bob was in a relationship with a woman named Ruth Tyrangiel this could be her or that could be her all I know is they were together for about 17 years and she was considered his common law wife here's where things get messy because around the same time he was in a relationship with his backup singer named Carolyn Dennis together they had a daughter they named Desiree and then they got married in secret no one knew about it until they filed for divorce no one knew they had another daughter Carolyn said they purposely left his last name off of the birth certificate so that Desiree could decide to add it if she wanted to later she also said that implying that he kept Desiree a secret was a huge insult and that he was a great father to her all I know is people have been obsessed with who he's dated some say Edie Sedgwick he denies it he had a thing with singer Nico apparently he asked Mavis Staples to marry him she said no he was a ladies man Bob Dylan is a living legend and I cannot wait to see this movie A Complete Unknown

learned about his parents how he grew up he went to Cornell then he went to Juilliard here he met Robin Williams they had a lifelong friendship boom he's hired for Superman the hottest Clark Kent he's filming in London where he meets Gae Exton they begin a relationship because his parents‚Äô relationship was not a great example Christopher could not commit but he was living in London with Gae together they had two children son Matthew and daughter Alexandra Christopher is busier and busier doing Superman's 1 2 3 and 4 in 1987 Gae and Christopher decide to separate he moves back to the US and he sees his children on holidays later that same year Christopher meets a young singer actress named Dana Morosini they were a couple living together but again Christopher had commitment issues Christopher was Superman he was 6‚Äô4 buff athletic very physical he was a pilot he wind surfed sailed boats he learned how to ride horses for a project he was in even though he was allergic after about five years Christopher finally decided to propose to Dana and they got married in 1992 later that same year they had a son they named William in this documentary they talk about the tragic accident that happened in 1995 he was competing at a horse show when right before the third jump his horse just refused completely stopped Christopher was thrown off the horse fell directly on his head broken snapped just like a noose half an inch to the left he would have been gone half an inch to the right he would have just gotten up his first and second vertebrae completely destroyed his spinal cord was severely damaged he was paralyzed from the neck down could not breathe without a ventilator this documentary talks about how his own mother wanted to pull the plug and he wanted to with the help of Robin Williams and his wife and Christopher's wife Dana Christopher Reeve was able to make an appearance at the 1996 Oscars watching this reminded me to be grateful for your health for all of the little things does anyone remember this Super Bowl commercial from the year 2000 where Christopher Reeve looked like he was walking on his own two feet my jaw was on the floor and then come to find out it wasn't real it was just a commercial for some *investment* company I was bawling tears even looking at this I wanna cry Christopher Reeve was only 52 when he passed away in 2004 from cardiac arrest less than a year later his wife Dana was diagnosed with lung cancer even though she never smoked a year and a half after Christopher passed away Dana passed away leaving Will without parents at 13 years old this was so well done I'm still recovering his children are gorgeous and Will  is on Good Morning America to make your heart ache even more someone in this film says if Christopher was still alive Robin still would be too
